{"id":"news_app-g3p","title":"Refactor navigation stack to prevent invalid path updates","description":"Centralize navigation handling to avoid NavigationColumnState.boundPathChange assertions: (1) move to a single NavigationStack coordinator for content detail routes, removing/isolating nested NavigationStacks in Favorites/Search/Chats where possible; (2) gate path mutations (append/replace/clear) on the main actor with deduping and state guards; (3) delay reading-state restore until list view models finish initial load to avoid pushing missing destinations.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-11-29T16:32:47.01643-08:00","updated_at":"2025-11-29T16:32:47.01643-08:00","labels":["crash","ios"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"news_app-g3p","depends_on_id":"news_app-j3d","type":"blocks","created_at":"2025-11-29T16:33:51.352499-08:00","created_by":"willem"}]}
{"id":"news_app-j3d","title":"Investigate SwiftUI navigation crash (NavigationColumnState.boundPathChange)","description":"All four TestFlight reports (builds 38/41/43 on iPhone18,4 / iOS 26.1) crash with EXC_BREAKPOINT in NavigationColumnState.boundPathChange -\u003e NavigationState.update when NavigationStack path is mutated. Reproduce on device/simulator, instrument ContentView navigation path updates and tab switching, and identify which flow (content restore, tab change, favorites, etc.) feeds an invalid path update. Crash logs stored under logs/testflight_feedback/*/crashlog.crash.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-11-29T16:32:31.366745-08:00","updated_at":"2025-11-29T16:34:18.909702-08:00","labels":["crash","ios"]}
